# Environment Variables for Patient Portal Vercel Deployment

## Required Environment Variables

### Supabase Configuration
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=your_supabase_url_here
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your_supabase_anon_key_here
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=your_supabase_service_role_key_here

### Kinde Authentication
KINDE_CLIENT_ID=your_kinde_client_id_here
KINDE_CLIENT_SECRET=your_kinde_client_secret_here
KINDE_ISSUER_URL=your_kinde_issuer_url_here

# IMPORTANT: Update these URLs for production deployment
KINDE_SITE_URL=https://patient-portal.vercel.app
KINDE_POST_LOGOUT_REDIRECT_URL=https://patient-portal.vercel.app
KINDE_POST_LOGIN_REDIRECT_URL=https://patient-portal.vercel.app/dashboard

### Gemini AI
NEXT_PUBLIC_GEMINI_API_KEY=your_gemini_api_key_here

### ZegoCloud (Video Calls)
NEXT_PUBLIC_ZEGO_APP_ID=your_zego_app_id_here
NEXT_PUBLIC_ZEGO_SERVER_SECRET=your_zego_server_secret_here

## Instructions for Vercel Deployment

1. Go to your Vercel project settings
2. Navigate to "Environment Variables"
3. Add each variable above with your actual values
4. Make sure to set them for "Production", "Preview", and "Development" environments
5. Redeploy after adding all variables

## Security Notes

- Never commit this file with actual values to git
- Keep your service role key and secrets secure
- Update Kinde callback URLs in Kinde dashboard to match your Vercel domain
